<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/643588-i-m-debating-reading-it-for-the-strangest">I&#39;m debating reading it for the strangest reason. The author. I don&#39;t know if I can stand reading about an old author trying to interpret teenagers. Because the thing is, when they were teenagers things were completely different. If someone is younger then they will probably have a better memory of teenagers and they will be a fresh voice who can connect immensely to their readers. Should I give it a chance?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_643588'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F41424.Beauty">like</a></span>

